definition.value: A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol that has pentadecanoyl as 1- and 2-acyl groups.

A member of the class of pyridopyrimidines that is 2-methyl-6,7,8,9-tetrahydropyrido[1,2-a]pyrimidin-4-one carrying an additional 2-[4-(6-fluoro-1,2-benzoxazol-3-yl)piperidin-1-yl]ethyl group at position 2.
A trihydroxybenzoic acid that is benzoic acid substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 2, 3, and 4.

A steroid glucosiduronic acid that is 5alpha-androstane-3beta,17beta-diol having a single beta-D-glucuronic acid residue attached at position 3. It is a biochemical marker of peripheral tissue androgen metabolism.
